23.  ‘olfactory  board  game’  means  a  toy  the  purpose  of  which  is to 
assist a child to learn to recognise different odours or flavours; 
24.  ‘cosmetic kit’ means a toy the purpose of which is to assist a child 
to  learn  to  make  products  such  as  fragrances,  soaps,  creams, 
shampoos,  bath  foams,  glosses,  lipsticks,  other  make-up, 
tooth-paste and conditioners;

25.  ‘gustative  game’  means  a  toy  the  purpose  of  which  is  to  allow 
children to make sweets or dishes which involve the use of food 
ingredients such as sweets, liquids, powders and aromas;

26.  ‘harm’  means  physical  injury  or  any  other  damage  to  health, 
including long-term health effects;

27.  ‘hazard’ means a potential source of harm; 
